chHWType.name: chHWType
chHWType.description: Indicates type of enclosure in which the LANNET SNMP agent operates.

chNumberOfSlots.name: chNumberOfSlots
chNumberOfSlots.description: Number of manageable slots in the chassis. In LANNET implementation it describes the number of manageable slots in the chassis (not all slots should be ocuppied).

chNumberOfEthernetBuses.name: chNumberOfEthernetBuses
chNumberOfEthernetBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Ethernet buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfTRBuses.name: chNumberOfTRBuses
chNumberOfTRBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Token Ring buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfFDDIBuses.name: chNumberOfFDDIBuses
chNumberOfFDDIBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal FDDI buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses.name: chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses
chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Local Talk buses provided by the box.

chReset.name: chReset
chReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a reset command for the whole chassis. It initiates a complete reinitialisation of the chassis and of all the devices incorporated inside the chassis.

chFullConfig.name: chFullConfig
chFullConfig.description: Full configuration message retrieved by LANNET management stations at periodic interrogation times. Coded in compact internal LANNET application format.

chGenAgTable.name: chGenAgTable
chGenAgTable.description: Table of configuration attributes common to all SNMP agents in LANNET hubs.

chGenAgEntry.name: chGenAgEntry
chGenAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single agent.

chGenAgId.name: chGenAgId
chGenAgId.description: Agent index for identifying the agent.Takes the value of the slot number where the agent card is inserted. For box agents the value of chGenAgId is chNumberOfSlots+1.

chGenAgMgmtIfType.name: chGenAgMgmtIfType
chGenAgMgmtIfType.description: This attribute describes one of the interfaces of agents existing on LANNET modules and their type. Value 'none' defines the lack of an interface recognized by the management console. Any other value defines an interface whose type is recognized by the management console and may be used as a management channel.

chGenAgAddr.name: chGenAgAddr
chGenAgAddr.description: This attribute defines an unique address by which the agent may be addressed by the management console. The address format should be consistent with the type defined by chGenAgMgmtIfType.

chGenAgSpecificOID.name: chGenAgSpecificOID
chGenAgSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

chLntAgTable.name: chLntAgTable
chLntAgTable.description: Table of configuration attributes of LANNET SNMP box agents in LANNET hubs.

chLntAgEntry.name: chLntAgEntry
chLntAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single agent.

chLntAgId.name: chLntAgId
chLntAgId.description: Agent index for identifying the agent. Identical to the index in chGenAgTable for the described agent.

chLntAgSLIPAddress.name: chLntAgSLIPAddress
chLntAgSLIPAddress.description: IP address of the SLIP channel of the agent

chLntAgSWVersion.name: chLntAgSWVersion
chLntAgSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent software version.

chLntAgKernelVersion.name: chLntAgKernelVersion
chLntAgKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent operating system (kernel) version.

chLntAgCoprocSWVersion.name: chLntAgCoprocSWVersion
chLntAgCoprocSWVersion.description: ASCII string describing the software version of the agent's coprocessor.

chLntAgSWFault.name: chLntAgSWFault
chLntAgSWFault.description: System fault emitted by agent software. It covers faults detected by the agent operating system and drivers. EnterpriseSpecific traps mechanism is used for transfering these traps to the management system.

chLntAgMgmtBusSelection.name: chLntAgMgmtBusSelection
chLntAgMgmtBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the number of the bus on which management data are reported.

chLntAgCoprocCommStatus.name: chLntAgCoprocCommStatus
chLntAgCoprocCommStatus.description: Attribute describing the status of the communication between the agent and its coprocessor.

chLntAgCommDebugMode.name: chLntAgCommDebugMode
chLntAgCommDebugMode.description: Attribute describing the agent mode in which communication problem traps are sent to managers (value 'on') or are not sent to managers (value 'off').

chLntAgConfigChangeTraps.name: chLntAgConfigChangeTraps
chLntAgConfigChangeTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Configuration Change traps to the manager.

chLntAgFaultTraps.name: chLntAgFaultTraps
chLntAgFaultTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Fault traps to the manager.

chLntAgTrafficThreshTraps.name: chLntAgTrafficThreshTraps
chLntAgTrafficThreshTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Traffic Threshold traps to the manager.

chLntAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps.name: chLntAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps
chLntAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Group Enrollment and Group Deenrollment traps to the manager.

chLntAgSoftFaultTraps.name: chLntAgSoftFaultTraps
chLntAgSoftFaultTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Software Fault traps to the manager.

chLntAgHubEnrollTraps.name: chLntAgHubEnrollTraps
chLntAgHubEnrollTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends periodic Hub Enrollment traps to the manager.

chLntAgTempThreshTraps.name: chLntAgTempThreshTraps
chLntAgTempThreshTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Temperature Threshold traps to the manager.

chLntAgSpecificOID.name: chLntAgSpecificOID
chLntAgSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

chLntAgLastAddrConfig.name: chLntAgLastAddrConfig
chLntAgLastAddrConfig.description: Configuration attribute describing the last physical address detected at each port. Coded in internal LANNET application format.

chLntAgSecAddrConfig.name: chLntAgSecAddrConfig
chLntAgSecAddrConfig.description: Configuration attribute describing the configuration of the secure addresses. Coded in internal LANNET application format.

chLntAgSoftwareStatus.name: chLntAgSoftwareStatus
chLntAgSoftwareStatus.description: Describes configuration of the firmware on this agent. unLoadable(1) - is returned by agents which do not support the Software Download feature; loaded(2) - is returned by agents with loaded software; downLoading(3) - when the attribute is set to this value by manager, it triggers the Software Download procedure. When procedure finished, agent software will restablish value loaded(2).

chLntAgConfigurationSymbol.name: chLntAgConfigurationSymbol
chLntAgConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by LANNET. One single character A..Z defines the CS version. For older modules which did not support this option on SNMP character '*' will be returned.

chLntAgIntTemp.name: chLntAgIntTemp
chLntAgIntTemp.description: Internal temperature measured by the temperature sensor placed on the agent card. Expressed in Celsius degrees.

chLntAgBootVersion.name: chLntAgBootVersion
chLntAgBootVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent boot software version.

chMgrTrapRepStatus.name: chMgrTrapRepStatus
chMgrTrapRepStatus.description: Value 'on' indicates that SNMP agent should send SNMP traps (traffic ex- cluded) to the manager.

chMgrContPerfRep.name: chMgrContPerfRep
chMgrContPerfRep.description: Value 'on' indicates that the SNMP agent should send traffic SNMP traps to the manager.

chMgrMngmtState.name: chMgrMngmtState
chMgrMngmtState.description: Attribute to be set by manager in order to instruct the agent to enter into a management session with the console. Setting this value to 'on' has the effect of performing an 'I am your manager' action upon the agent.

chHWPSUTable.name: chHWPSUTable
chHWPSUTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for Power Supply Units. This table can be retrieved only from agents equipped with adequate hardware.

chHWPSUEntry.name: chHWPSUEntry
chHWPSUEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single Power Supply Unit.

chHWPSUId.name: chHWPSUId
chHWPSUId.description: PSU index for identifying the PSU.

chHWPSUActivityStatus.name: chHWPSUActivityStatus
chHWPSUActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of the PSU in what concerns supplying power to the chassis. NotActive - indicates a disabled or defective PSU which cannot supply power to the chassis. Dormant - indicates a functional PSU which is installed for backup purposes and can at any moment supply power to the devices in the chassis. Active - indicates that the PSU supplies power to the chassis.

chHWPSULocation.name: chHWPSULocation
chHWPSULocation.description: Describes the location (internal or external) of the PSU.

chHWPSUVoltage.name: chHWPSUVoltage
chHWPSUVoltage.description: Indicates voltage of PSU expressed in miliVolts.

chHWIntTempWarning.name: chHWIntTempWarning
chHWIntTempWarning.description: Fault condition indicating that the temperature measured by one of the sensors internal to the box exceeded chHWIntTempThresh.

chHWIntTempThresh.name: chHWIntTempThresh
chHWIntTempThresh.description: Internal enclosure temperature threshold value, expressed in degrees Celsius. When exceeded, a trap is sent to the management console.

chHWPeakIntTemp.name: chHWPeakIntTemp
chHWPeakIntTemp.description: Maximum internal temperature inside the chassis. It is the maximum of the temperature values detected by different temperature sensors inside the box.

genGroupTable.name: genGroupTable
genGroupTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for managed LANNET modules. Includes configuration data which are independent of the specific functionality of the module.

genGroupEntry.name: genGroupEntry
genGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single group.

genGroupId.name: genGroupId
genGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genGroupSWVersion.name: genGroupSWVersion
genGroupSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the group software version.

genGroupKernelVersion.name: genGroupKernelVersion
genGroupKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the group kernel version.

genGroupType.name: genGroupType
genGroupType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET Ethernet group.

genGroupDescr.name: genGroupDescr
genGroupDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

genGroupNumberOfPorts.name: genGroupNumberOfPorts
genGroupNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports in group. It is assumed that on each group the ports are assigned unique numbers in the range from 1 to genGroupNumberOfPorts. They correspond to the number of ports on the module (FRU)

genGroupNumberOfIntPorts.name: genGroupNumberOfIntPorts
genGroupNumberOfIntPorts.description: Number of internal ports (ports connected to the chassis buses) on the module.

genGroupReset.name: genGroupReset
genGroupReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to 'on' is interpreted as a software RESET command. Sensor software is reinitialized and according to the sensor specifications, partial or total reset of the module hardware may be performed.

genGroupAutoMan.name: genGroupAutoMan
genGroupAutoMan.description: This attribute reflects the status of the Auto/Manual switch which defines the working mode of LANNET sensors. In the MANUAL mode no set operations may be performed on attributes related to the sensor. The sensor works according to configuration switches set by hardware and transmits all configuration information to the agent. In the AUTO mode, hardware switches are overridden by set commands.

genGroupFullConfig.name: genGroupFullConfig
genGroupFullConfig.description: Attribute describing the full configuration of a group in internal LANNET application format.

genGroupRedun12.name: genGroupRedun12
genGroupRedun12.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 1 and 2 on a LANNET module.

genGroupRedun34.name: genGroupRedun34
genGroupRedun34.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 3 and 4 on a LANNET module.

genGroupRedun13_14.name: genGroupRedun13_14
genGroupRedun13_14.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 13 and 14 on a LANNET module.

genGroupStandAloneMode.name: genGroupStandAloneMode
genGroupStandAloneMode.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates the sensor's operation Stand Alone mode . Internal ports are disabled and the card functions in a local star configuration toward its external ports.

genGroupInterProcCommStatus.name: genGroupInterProcCommStatus
genGroupInterProcCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the communication between the microprocessor of the sensor and the microprocessor of the agent on cards with embedded agents.

genGroupCommStatus.name: genGroupCommStatus
genGroupCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the communication status of the group with the SNMP Agent as detected and reported by the agent.

genGroupHWStatus.name: genGroupHWStatus
genGroupHWStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

genGroupSupplyVoltageFault.name: genGroupSupplyVoltageFault
genGroupSupplyVoltageFault.description: A value 'on' of this attribute informs of a 'voltage supply out-of-range' error condition on sensor equipped with hardware which checks this condition.

genGroupIntTemp.name: genGroupIntTemp
genGroupIntTemp.description: Internal temperature of the enclosure as measured by the specific module instance.

genGroupSpecificOID.name: genGroupSpecificOID
genGroupSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

genGroupConfigurationSymbol.name: genGroupConfigurationSymbol
genGroupConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by LANNET. One single character A..Z defines the CS version. For older modules which did not support this option on SNMP character '*' will be returned.

genPortTable.name: genPortTable
genPortTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for managed LANNET ports. Includes configuration data which are independent of the specific functionality of the port.

genPortEntry.name: genPortEntry
genPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single port.

genPortGroupId.name: genPortGroupId
genPortGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group containing the port is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genPortId.name: genPortId
genPortId.description: Index which identifies the port inside the group for which this entry contains information. It generally corresponds with the number by which the port is identified and is marked on the module. This value is never greater than genGroupNumberOfPorts of the group to which the port belongs.

genPortFunctionality.name: genPortFunctionality
genPortFunctionality.description: Describes the functionality of the port according to international standards.

genPortType.name: genPortType
genPortType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET port.

genPortDescr.name: genPortDescr
genPortDescr.description: Descriptor of the port in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

genPortActivityStatus.name: genPortActivityStatus
genPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of ports that may be part of a redundancy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive packets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive packets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

genPortSecurityPolicy.name: genPortSecurityPolicy
genPortSecurityPolicy.description: Security policy (Trap Only or Trap and Close) assigned to this port. The information is coded in internal LANNET format.

genPortSecureAddresses.name: genPortSecureAddresses
genPortSecureAddresses.description: This attribute defines the security information (physical addresses) relevant for the entry. Coded in internal format, cryptographic methods may be used for privacy purposes.

genPortIntPortConnection.name: genPortIntPortConnection
genPortIntPortConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the internal port to which the port is connected. A value 0 of this attribute would indicate no internal port connection (stand-alone mode). Any other positive value equals the number of the internal port.

genPortAdminStatus.name: genPortAdminStatus
genPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits nor receives. The port must be explici- tenly enabled to restore operation. For token ring ports, this attribute is read-only.

genPortSpecificOID.name: genPortSpecificOID
genPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

genIntPortTable.name: genIntPortTable
genIntPortTable.description: Table of configuration attributes of LANNET internal ports. Internal ports are physical and/or logical entities which transfer information and connect LANNET modules to the internal networks (buses).

genIntPortEntry.name: genIntPortEntry
genIntPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single port.

genIntPortGroupId.name: genIntPortGroupId
genIntPortGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group containing the internal port is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genIntPortId.name: genIntPortId
genIntPortId.description: Index which identifies the port inside the group for which this entry contains information. This value is never greater than genGroupNumberOfIntPorts of the group to which the port belongs.

genIntPortAdminStatus.name: genIntPortAdminStatus
genIntPortAdminStatus.description: Defines the capability of the internal port to transmit or receive data. A disabled internal port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitly enabled to restore operation.

genIntPortActivityStatus.name: genIntPortActivityStatus
genIntPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of internal ports that may be part of a redundancy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive packets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive packets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible for packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

genIntPortBusConnNumber.name: genIntPortBusConnNumber
genIntPortBusConnNumber.description: The value of this attribute defines the bus to which the internal port is connected.

genIntPortBusConnType.name: genIntPortBusConnType
genIntPortBusConnType.description: The value of this attribute defines the type of the bus to which the internal port is connected.

genIntPortSpecificOID.name: genIntPortSpecificOID
genIntPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

softRedundancyTable.name: softRedundancyTable
softRedundancyTable.description: Table of attributes which define software redundancy links defined by means of the LANNET chassis SNMP agents.

softRedundancyEntry.name: softRedundancyEntry
softRedundancyEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single software redundancy link.

softRedundancyId.name: softRedundancyId
softRedundancyId.description: Index which identifies the software redundancy link which for which the current entry provides information.

softRedundancyName.name: softRedundancyName
softRedundancyName.description: Logical name of the software redundancy link

softRedundancyGroupId1.name: softRedundancyGroupId1
softRedundancyGroupId1.description: ID of the group to which the main port on the software redundancy link belongs. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

softRedundancyPortId1.name: softRedundancyPortId1
softRedundancyPortId1.description: ID of the main port on the software redundancy link.

softRedundancyGroupId2.name: softRedundancyGroupId2
softRedundancyGroupId2.description: ID of the group to which the secondary port on the software redundancy link belongs. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

softRedundancyPortId2.name: softRedundancyPortId2
softRedundancyPortId2.description: ID of the secondary port on the software redundancy link.

softRedundancyStatus.name: softRedundancyStatus
softRedundancyStatus.description: Status of the entry in the softRedundancy Table: valid(1) indicates that row is busy with meaningful values; createRequest(2) will be set by manager when creating a new row; underCreation(3) indicates that agent accepts create command and performs it; invalid(4) indicates that no meaningful values are present in the row. Managers set this value in order to transmit a 'Delete row' command to agent.

ethAgTable.name: ethAgTable
ethAgTable.description: Table of attributes which define configuration characteristics for LANNET chassis SNMP agents which use Ethernet as in-band management protocol.

ethAgEntry.name: ethAgEntry
ethAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single Ethernet agent.

ethAgId.name: ethAgId
ethAgId.description: Index which identifies the Ethernet agent for which the current entry provides information.

ethAgPerfBusSelection.name: ethAgPerfBusSelection
ethAgPerfBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the bus attached to the performance data collection hardware on those LANNET agent hardware implementations which support configuration management on multi-Ethernet bus enclosures, but performan- ce data collection on a single bus.

ethGroupTable.name: ethGroupTable
ethGroupTable.description: Table of attributes which define configuration characteristics for LANNET Ethernet modules.

ethGroupEntry.name: ethGroupEntry
ethGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single Ethernet module (group).

ethGroupId.name: ethGroupId
ethGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

ethGroupFIFO.name: ethGroupFIFO
ethGroupFIFO.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal FIFO error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a LANNET repeater.

ethGroup10BTPlus.name: ethGroup10BTPlus
ethGroup10BTPlus.description: Value ON of this attribute defines activation of the 10BaseTPlus mode - a LANNET extension of the 10BaseT standard.

ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy.name: ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy
ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between internal ports 1 and 2 on a LANNET module.

ethGroupBackboneMode.name: ethGroupBackboneMode
ethGroupBackboneMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines Backbone Mode of a sensor. Internal ports are enabled and the information path goes straightly from external port to internal bus, via corresponding internal port.

ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode.name: ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode
ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines FOIRL of a sensor. When this attribute has value ON, FOIRL Plus mode is enabled, while value OFF indicates stan- dard FOIRL mode.

ethGroupWrongPortSelection.name: ethGroupWrongPortSelection
ethGroupWrongPortSelection.description: A value ON of this attribute warns of incorrect selection of enabled ports on sensors which impose restrictions on this configura- tion (e.g. integrated local bridges.)

ethGroupBackupBus.name: ethGroupBackupBus
ethGroupBackupBus.description: Defines the common secondary bus for Ethernet groups with bus redundancy defined at port level.

ethGroupSingleBusMode.name: ethGroupSingleBusMode
ethGroupSingleBusMode.description: Value 'on of this attribute defines bus-star mode for cards supporting this type of configuration.

ethGroupSpecificOID.name: ethGroupSpecificOID
ethGroupSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

ethPortGroupId.name: ethPortGroupId
ethPortGroupId.description: Id of the group to which the port belongs.

ethPortId.name: ethPortId
ethPortId.description: Unique Id of the port in the ethPortTable.

ethPortFunctionalStatus.name: ethPortFunctionalStatus
ethPortFunctionalStatus.description: The value of this attribute reflects the functional status of LANNET synchronous ports. Note that it is not mandatory that all ports support all the enumerated states. Here is the minimal set possible states: OK - fully functional port, transmitting and receiving packets. RLD - receive link down condition on the port. TLD - transmit link down condition on the port. LocalJabber - fault condition indicating that the port emitted jabber. RemoteJabber - fault condition indicating that remote jabber was sensed at the port. IllSeq - Fault condition indicating an illegal synchronization sequence at the port. ShortCircuit - short-circuit fault condition detected at the port. PartitionOrLocalJabber - RemoteFaultOrLockLoss -

ethPortManPart.name: ethPortManPart
ethPortManPart.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON activates the manual partition mechanism at the port level. Setting the value of this attribute to OFF cancels the partition mechanism. The segment may reconnect after the reception of 32 packets. Attribute vaild for repeater modules from the LE-10 family.

ethPortJabber.name: ethPortJabber
ethPortJabber.description: Value ON of this attribute reflects jabber transmitted to the port by the hardware of a LANNET repeater or transceiver, as a result of collisions detected on the port. Valid for all modules in the LE-10 and LE-15 families.

ethPortNoAUILoop.name: ethPortNoAUILoop
ethPortNoAUILoop.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates that a No AUI Loop fault condition was detected on an AUI repeater port. Valid for LE-10C family of modu- les.

ethPortMJLP.name: ethPortMJLP
ethPortMJLP.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal MJLP (MAU Jabber Lockup Protection) error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a LANNET repeater. Valid for LE140XTF.

ethPortFIFO.name: ethPortFIFO
ethPortFIFO.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal FIFO error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a LANNET repeater. Valid for LE140XTF.

ethPortAutoPartitionState.name: ethPortAutoPartitionState
ethPortAutoPartitionState.description: The AutoPart condition indicates that the port is currently partitioned by the auto-partition protection mechanism.

ethPortSQETest.name: ethPortSQETest
ethPortSQETest.description: Settable attribute which allows activation of SQE test for LANNET integrated transceivers.

ethPortLastSourceAddr.name: ethPortLastSourceAddr
ethPortLastSourceAddr.description: Ethernet source address of the last readable frame received by this port.

ethPortUserStatus.name: ethPortUserStatus
ethPortUserStatus.description: Attribute defining the connection of a port to a single Ethernet source or to a multi-source (segment or star).

ethPortMainBusSelection.name: ethPortMainBusSelection
ethPortMainBusSelection.description: On cards with port-level redundancy, defines the main bus for each port instance as selected by user.

ethPortTraffic.name: ethPortTraffic
ethPortTraffic.description: Counter for the number of bits received on this port in frames with legal length information.

ethPortFramesReceivedOK.name: ethPortFramesReceivedOK
ethPortFramesReceivedOK.description: A representation of the total number of frames of legal length that have not been corrupted in transmission. These frames can be encoded and decoded by the commonly available MACs and provide a measure of the network bandwidth being used. The number does not include frames received with frame-too-long, FCS, alignment errors, frames lost due to internal MAC sublayer errors, runts or pygmys.

ethPortRunts.name: ethPortRunts
ethPortRunts.description: Counter for the number of collision fragments longer than a pygmy and shorter than a legal packet, detected on this port.

ethPortPacketErrors.name: ethPortPacketErrors
ethPortPacketErrors.description: Counter for the number of frames with errors detected on the port by the LANNET agent hardware. This generic port error comprises too long packets, CRC and alignment errors.

ethPortSpecificOID.name: ethPortSpecificOID
ethPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

ethIntPortGroupId.name: ethIntPortGroupId
ethIntPortGroupId.description: ID of the group to which the internal port belongs.

ethIntPortId.name: ethIntPortId
ethIntPortId.description: ID of the internal port in the ethIntPortTable.

ethIntPortPartition.name: ethIntPortPartition
ethIntPortPartition.description: This condition indicates that the internal port is currently partitioned from the bus by the auto-partition protection mechanism.

ethIntPortJabber.name: ethIntPortJabber
ethIntPortJabber.description: Value ON of this attribute reflects jabber being transmitted to the bus by the hardware of a LANNET repeater, as a result of collisions detected on the internal bus of the enclosure. This situation is similar to MJLP as defined by the Repeater Management standard.

ethIntPortBackedUp.name: ethIntPortBackedUp
ethIntPortBackedUp.description: Indicates that internal port is part of a redundancy scheme.

ethBusPerfAgId.name: ethBusPerfAgId
ethBusPerfAgId.description: ID of the agent in the ethBusPerfTable.

ethBusPerfId.name: ethBusPerfId
ethBusPerfId.description: ID of the bus in the ethBusPerfTable.

ethBusTrafficBuffer.name: ethBusTrafficBuffer
ethBusTrafficBuffer.description: Record of traffic for the last second with a resolution of 100 msec. The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic and each record contains 10 readings, in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale ( value = 10*log10(percent) ).

ethBusTrafficThresh.name: ethBusTrafficThresh
ethBusTrafficThresh.description: Traffic threshold value. When exceeded, a trap is send to the management console. Expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic, in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale.

ethBusPeakTraffic.name: ethBusPeakTraffic
ethBusPeakTraffic.description: Maximal traffic value since last reset of hub or relay. Expressed in per- cents of the maximum Ethernet traffic, in the range 1..20, expressed on log(10) scale.

ethBusTotalCollisions.name: ethBusTotalCollisions
ethBusTotalCollisions.description: Counter incremented every time the hub enters a condition caused by simultaneous transmission and detection of external activity on one or more of its ports.

ethBusTotalPackets.name: ethBusTotalPackets
ethBusTotalPackets.description: Counter for number of packets (good and errors) detected on the Ethernet bus.

ethBusTotalErrors.name: ethBusTotalErrors
ethBusTotalErrors.description: Counter for number of errors detected on the Ethernet bus. Does not take into account the collisions.

ethBusTraffic.name: ethBusTraffic
ethBusTraffic.description: Last traffic reading (sampling time = 100 msec). The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale ( value = 10*log10(percent) ).

ethBusClockBusId.name: ethBusClockBusId
ethBusClockBusId.description: ID of the bus in the ethBusClockTable.

ethBusClockId.name: ethBusClockId
ethBusClockId.description: ID of the clock in the ethBusClockTable.

ethBusClockTestResult.name: ethBusClockTestResult
ethBusClockTestResult.description: Values clockFailure and busFailure define the faulty statuses for clock tests. The test is performed by LCL100 module.

tokRingAgId.name: tokRingAgId
tokRingAgId.description: ID of the agent to which the ring belongs in the tokRingTable.

tokRingId.name: tokRingId
tokRingId.description: ID of the ring in the tokRingTable.

tokRingLeftSlot.name: tokRingLeftSlot
tokRingLeftSlot.description: Slot number of the left-most slot of the ring.

tokRingRightSlot.name: tokRingRightSlot
tokRingRightSlot.description: Slot number of the right-most slot of the ring.

tokRingTrafficBuffer.name: tokRingTrafficBuffer
tokRingTrafficBuffer.description: Record of traffic for the last second with a resolution of 100 msec. The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded) and each record contains 10 readings, in range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

tokRingTrafficThresh.name: tokRingTrafficThresh
tokRingTrafficThresh.description: Traffic threshold value. When exceeded, a trap is send to the management console. Expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded) in the range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

tokRingPeakTraffic.name: tokRingPeakTraffic
tokRingPeakTraffic.description: Maximal traffic value since last reset of agent. Expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded), in the range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

tokRingNumberOfStations.name: tokRingNumberOfStations
tokRingNumberOfStations.description: Number of Token Ring stations (controllers) detected on the ring. The TR controller of the agent card is included in this count.

tokRingConfiguration.name: tokRingConfiguration
tokRingConfiguration.description: Configuration attribute describing the list of physical addresses detected on the Token Ring. Coded in internal LANNET application format.

tokRingBeaconing.name: tokRingBeaconing
tokRingBeaconing.description: This attribute indicates if a beaconing condition is currently detected on the ring.

tokRingBeaconingStation.name: tokRingBeaconingStation
tokRingBeaconingStation.description: The MAC address of the last station which was detected as sending Beaconing MAC frames on the ring.

tokRingStationsMatch.name: tokRingStationsMatch
tokRingStationsMatch.description: This attribute indicates matching between the number of stations detected on the ring between the current agent and the next agent on Up Stream sense and the number of connected lobe ports.Used by the port address correlation mechanism.

tokRingTraffic.name: tokRingTraffic
tokRingTraffic.description: Last traffic reading (sampling time = 100 msec). The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale ( value = 10*log10(percent) ).

tokGroupId.name: tokGroupId
tokGroupId.description: Number of the slot in which the group is installed.

tokGroupAutoRightLoop.name: tokGroupAutoRightLoop
tokGroupAutoRightLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop was automatically created on a Token Ring module which does not sense the existence of another token ring group on the right hand side.

tokGroupAutoLeftLoop.name: tokGroupAutoLeftLoop
tokGroupAutoLeftLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop was automatically created on a Token Ring module which does not sense the existence of another token ring group on the left hand side.

tokGroupManRightLoop.name: tokGroupManRightLoop
tokGroupManRightLoop.description: Setting this attribute to ON signifies a command to the hardware to create a loop on the Token Ring module which isolates the ring from the right hand side.

tokGroupManLeftLoop.name: tokGroupManLeftLoop
tokGroupManLeftLoop.description: Setting this attribute to ON signifies a command to the hardware to create a loop on the Token Ring module which isolates the ring from the left hand side.

tokGroupRightNeighbor.name: tokGroupRightNeighbor
tokGroupRightNeighbor.description: Attribute defining the existence of a neighbor another token ring group on the right hand side of the module.

tokGroupLeftNeighbor.name: tokGroupLeftNeighbor
tokGroupLeftNeighbor.description: Attribute defining the existence of a neighbor another token ring group on the left hand side of the module.

tokGroupIOMode.name: tokGroupIOMode
tokGroupIOMode.description: Attribute defining the I/O mode (single, dual-ring-in, dual-ring-out) Lobe, Internal Repeater or Star) of a module from the the LTR-IO family.

tokGroupBridgeMode.name: tokGroupBridgeMode
tokGroupBridgeMode.description: Attribute describing the operational mode of the bridge. For ITLB the following modes are defined: - Mode A: First channel connected to an external ring (RI,RO connectors) and second channel connected to an internal ring; - Mode B: First channel connected to an external ring by a DTE connector and second channel connected to an internal ring; - Mode C: First channel connected to an internal left ring and second channel connected to an internal right ring.

tokGroupManLinkLoop.name: tokGroupManLinkLoop
tokGroupManLinkLoop.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON instructs the hardware of a LANNET Token Ring repeater module to close the loop in the direction of the external connection.

tokGroupManBusLoop.name: tokGroupManBusLoop
tokGroupManBusLoop.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON instructs the hardware of a LANNET Token Ring repeater module to close the loop in the direction of the internal bus.

tokGroupAutoLinkLoop.name: tokGroupAutoLinkLoop
tokGroupAutoLinkLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop has been auto- matically closed by the hardwar of the LANNET Token Ring repeater as a result of problems on the external link.

tokGroupAutoBusLoop.name: tokGroupAutoBusLoop
tokGroupAutoBusLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop has been auto- matically closed by the hardware of the LANNET Token Ring repeater as a result of problems on the internal bus.

tokGroupSpecificOID.name: tokGroupSpecificOID
tokGroupSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

tokGroupRingGroupId.name: tokGroupRingGroupId
tokGroupRingGroupId.description: ID of the group to which the ring belongs.

tokGroupRingSpeed.name: tokGroupRingSpeed
tokGroupRingSpeed.description: Attribute describing the bandwidth of the ring.

tokGroupRingInserted.name: tokGroupRingInserted
tokGroupRingInserted.description: Indicates that the bridge interface has inserted itself into the ring.

tokPortGroupId.name: tokPortGroupId
tokPortGroupId.description: ID of the group to which the token ring port belongs.

tokPortId.name: tokPortId
tokPortId.description: ID of the port in the tokPortTable.

tokPortBypass.name: tokPortBypass
tokPortBypass.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON causes the by- passing of the TokenRing LANNET port.

tokPortConnected.name: tokPortConnected
tokPortConnected.description: Attribute which describes the connection status of a Token Ring port (inclusion of the Token Ring controller in the ring).

tokPortTCP.name: tokPortTCP
tokPortTCP.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON causes the activation of the cable-fault detection mechanism.

tokPortCableFault.name: tokPortCableFault
tokPortCableFault.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies the detection of a cable-fault on this specific Token Ring port.

tokPortFunctionalStatus.name: tokPortFunctionalStatus
tokPortFunctionalStatus.description: The value of this attribute reflects the functional status of LANNET Token Ring ports. Note that it is not mandatory that a certain port support all the enumerated states. Here is the lest of the possible states: OK - fully functional port, transmitting and receiving packets. RLD - receive link down condition on the port. TLD - transmit link down condition on the port.

tokPortLastSourceAddr.name: tokPortLastSourceAddr
tokPortLastSourceAddr.description: MAC source address of the last readable frame received by this port.

tokPortSpecificOID.name: tokPortSpecificOID
tokPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

tsGroupId.name: tsGroupId
tsGroupId.description: Number of the slot in which the group is installed.

tsGroupLATStatus.name: tsGroupLATStatus
tsGroupLATStatus.description: Value ON of this attribute means that LAT protocol is Enabled on the LANNET Ethernet module.

tsGroupOperationMode.name: tsGroupOperationMode
tsGroupOperationMode.description: This attribute describes the operation mode of the module in a multiprocessor configuration sensor, as reported by interprocessors communication.

ltalkPortGroupId.name: ltalkPortGroupId
ltalkPortGroupId.description: Number of the group to which the port belongs.

ltalkPortId.name: ltalkPortId
ltalkPortId.description: ID of the port in the ltalkPortTable.

ltalkPortTest.name: ltalkPortTest
ltalkPortTest.description: A value ON of this attribute indicates that a port test should be performed upon the port defined by the attribute instance.

ltalkPortTestResult.name: ltalkPortTestResult
ltalkPortTestResult.description: Indicates the result of a port test performed on this port.

ltalkPortJam.name: ltalkPortJam
ltalkPortJam.description: An ON value of this attribute indicates a Jam error on the specific port.

clGroupId.name: clGroupId
clGroupId.description: Number of the slot in which the group is installed.

clGroupClockRedundancy.name: clGroupClockRedundancy
clGroupClockRedundancy.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between the internal and external clocks on the LCL100 module.

clGroupMainClock.name: clGroupMainClock
clGroupMainClock.description: Value of this attribute is an index into clPortTable, and defines the clock that should operate or a main clock in redundancy scheme. Serves as 'Clock selection' switch on the card.

clGroupTestClocks.name: clGroupTestClocks
clGroupTestClocks.description: A value ON of this attribute indicates that a test should be performed on all clock ports.

clPortGroupId.name: clPortGroupId
clPortGroupId.description: Number of the group to which the port belongs.

clPortId.name: clPortId
clPortId.description: ID of the port in the clPortTable.

clPortFunctionalStatus.name: clPortFunctionalStatus
clPortFunctionalStatus.description: Indicates whether the clock is faulty or not.
